messages.message: @Victor Zeng @Xindi Xu do you know why we got a `Spend limit exceeded` error for the app runs in the Human Review Cypress tests in the CI run (https://cloud.cypress.io/projects/cfhedy/runs/14723) on Paul’s PR?

<mailto:support-testing+org-admin@instabase.com|support-testing+org-admin@instabase.com> - this is a preexisting user so all runs will use the same license. We'll need to update the spend limit to something higher.
Actually, shouldn't we use the commercial license in this case? Maybe i'm looking at the wrong test case

this `Spend limit exceeded` error is relevant for the following failures in the linked Cypress CI run ^:
• apps/src/flow-review/__e2e__/aihub-results/field-editor.spec.ts
• apps/src/flow-review/__e2e__/aihub-results/file-list.spec.ts
• apps/src/flow-review/__e2e__/aihub-results/results-table.spec.ts
i agree we should be using the commercial license in this case, so i’m also confused :disappointed:

One of the errors:

Let's file a new bug ticket for the flow team.
